The paper discusses processes to automate the selection of appropriate algorithms for various matrix computations, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also focuses on checking for and certifying various matrix properties of black box matrices, which can be related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the use of superfast algorithms and matrix preconditioning can be related to computer science theory (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
